  "name": "Curse Blessing: Retributive Curse",
  "permission": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "feat",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 10th level, as a swift or immediate action, you can inflict a curse on any adjacent creature that scores a critical hit against you or deals precision damage to you. The target must succeed at a Will saving throw or be cursed. Select one of the following effects: the target takes a –2 penalty to one ability score of your choice (the ability cannot be reduced below 1); the target takes a –2 penalty on attack rolls, saving throws, ability checks, and skill checks; each turn, the target has a 25% chance of taking no action (otherwise, it acts normally). This curse lasts for 1 hour.</p>\n<p>A creature can be subjected to only one instance of retributive curse at a time. This otherwise functions as&nbsp;bestow curse.</p>",
